comment:
* Contains information on all available Nfc
 * antennas on an Android device as well as information
 * on the device itself in relation positioning of the
 * antennas.

variables.name: mDeviceWidth
variables.comment: Width of the device in millimeters.

variables.name: mDeviceHeight
variables.comment: Height of the device in millimeters.

variables.name: mAvailableNfcAntennas
variables.comment: All available Nfc Antennas on the device.

methods.name: public int getDeviceWidth()
methods.comment: * Width of the device in millimeters.

methods.name: public int getDeviceHeight()
methods.comment: * Height of the device in millimeters.

methods.name: public boolean isDeviceFoldable()
methods.comment:
* Whether the device is foldable. When the device is foldable,
     * the 0, 0 is considered to be bottom-left when the device is unfolded and
     * the screens are facing the user. For non-foldable devices 0, 0
     * is bottom-left when the user is facing the screen.

methods.name: public List<AvailableNfcAntenna> getAvailableNfcAntennas()
methods.comment: * Get all NFC antennas that exist on the device.
